Notepad Web bundles assets derived from NotepadNext:
  - .lua language definitions (public/lua/) — used to drive syntax highlighting
    via Wasmoon (Lua 5.4 in WASM).
  - Toolbar icon PNGs (public/icons/) — sourced from the NotepadNext toolbar
    icon set, which itself includes FamFamFam Silk icons (CC-BY 3.0, Mark James).

Notepad++ is the original editor that NotepadNext reimplements; Notepad Web
extends that lineage to the browser/Chrome-extension platform. Notepad++ and
NotepadNext are the works of their respective authors and are not affiliated with
Notepad Web.

For the full list of runtime and build-time third-party dependencies (CodeMirror 6,
Wasmoon, dockview, and others), see THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.md.
